# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Use DP to solve the problem, both of recursive version & iterative version.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
"different sequences are counted as different combinations."
It 's not combination problem, but a problem for permutations.

According to the description for example 1, this problem is a problem for permutations with repetition. Each element in the array nums can be chosen many times as you wish.

A real hint for C/C++ users, use unsigned! Even using long long it overflows, very strange! But try unsigned, it will be fine.

Though LC says "The test cases are generated so that the answer can fit in a 32-bit integer." It has no guarantees for intermediate values.

One useful testcase
