considering [-1,1] and target N, it can generate infinite conbinations for N. i.e,` [-1,1, 1(N times)]` and `[-1,1,-1,1,1(N times)]`.  we need to restrict the length of combinations.
here is my Java solution:
```
public int combinationSumFour2(int[] nums, int target,
                                    int length,
                                   Map<Integer, Integer> map,
                                   int maxLen) {
        if(length > maxLen) return 0;
        int count = 0;
        if(target == 0) count++;
        for(int num: nums){
            count += combinationSumFour2(nums, target - num, length+1, map, maxLen);
        }
        if(count == 0)
            return count;
        map.put(target, count);
        return count;
    }
```

