solutions.content:
There is a definite substructure to the problem. 

For example, for the set {**1, 2, 3**}, and target = 4:

NumCombination(4) =
NumCombination(3) (Because adding **1** to each such combination would give sum 4) +
NumCombination(2) (Because adding **2** to each such combination would give sum 4) +
NumCombination(1) (Becasue adding **3**... you get the idea!)

**Step 1: Brute force DFS** (Time Limit Exceeded)
```
int combinationSum4(int *n, int nsz, int target)    {
    int scnt = 0, i;    
    for (i = 0; i < nsz && target; ++i) {
		/* DFS, recursively apply the logic. */
         if (target - n[i] >= 0)		 
            scnt += combinationSum4(n, nsz, target - n[i]);
    }
    /* Handle case when target = 0. */
    return target ? scnt : 1  ;
}
```
 Works, but does not scale. O(nsz ^ target) complexity and we also repeat computation for sub-problems.

**Step 2:  DP + DFS** (Time Limit Exceeded)

We simply cache the result of an already calculated combination count.

```
uint64_t helper(int *n, int nsz, int target, uint64_t *dp) {
    int i;

	/* Return cached result. */
    if (dp[target]) return dp[target];

	for (i = 0; i < nsz && target; ++i) {
		/* Cache the result. */
        if (target - n[i] >= 0)
			dp[target] += helper(n, nsz, target - n[i], dp);
	}    	
    return dp[target];
}

int combinationSum4(int *n, int nsz, int target)    {
    int scnt = 0;
    uint64_t *dp = calloc(target + 1, sizeof(uint64_t));

    if (!dp) return 0;

	dp[0] = 1;
    scnt = helper(n, nsz, target, dp);
    free(dp);    

    return scnt;
}
```

With caching we optimize on computation, but complexity is still O(nsz ^ target)

**Step 3: DP + Bottom up** (0/4 mSec)

With bottom up approach we cache the results and also get O(nsz * target) complexity.

```
int combinationSum4(int *n, int nsz, int target)    {
    int scnt = 0, i, j;
    uint64_t *dp = calloc(target + 1, sizeof(uint64_t));
    if (!dp) return scnt;
    dp[0] = 1;
    for (i = 1; i <= target; ++i) {
        for (j = 0; j < nsz; ++j) {
            if (n[j] <= i)
                dp[i] += dp[i - n[j]];
        }
    }
    scnt = dp[target];
    free(dp);    
    return scnt;
}
```

