solutions.content:
I find that I was able to beat most python entries by using the following:
- top-down DP through DFS with memoisation (bottom-up DP would compute "dead-end" interim results - top-down DFS avoids these)
-  sorting (surprisingly many python entries don't do it)

```
class Solution:
    def combinationSum4(self, nums: List[int], target: int) -> int:
        ways = [1] + [-1]*target # -1 as a flag that the sum hasn't been computed
        nums.sort()  # this, actually, saves quite a bit of time (see break clause)
        def dfs (target):
            if ways[target] != -1: return ways[target] #memoisation: don't repeat interim results
            res = 0
            for i in nums:
                if i <= target:
                    res += dfs(target - i)
                else: break # the numbers only get higher: no reason to continue
            ways[target] = res
            return res
        return dfs(target)
```

